etailed medication administration records","Complete documentation of past medical history","List of all completed investigations","Summary of routine observations"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe most critical component of handover is \u003Cstrong\u003Eclear communication of clinical risks and pending tasks\u003C/strong\u003E. This ensures the receiving team is aware of potential deterioration and required actions, which is essential for patient safety.\u003C/p\u003E        \u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E        \u003Cul\u003E        \u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDetailed medication administration records\u003C/strong\u003E - While important, medication records are typically documented separately and readily accessible\u003C/li\u003E        \u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EComplete documentation of past medical history\u003C/strong\u003E - Background information is important but less critical than current risks and required actions\u003C/li\u003E        \u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EList of all completed investigations\u003C/strong\u003E - Completed tasks are less urgent than pending actions and potential risks\u003C/li\u003E        \u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESummary of routine observations\u003C/strong\u003E - While relevant, trending and abnormal observations are more important than routine measurements\u003C/li\u003E    \u003C/ul\u003E        \u003Cp\u003EA safe handover should include:\u003C/p\u003E    \u003Cul\u003E        \u003Cli\u003EPatient identification and location\u003C/li\u003E        \u003Cli\u003ECurrent clinical concerns and early warning signs\u003C/li\u003E        \u003Cli\u003EOutstanding tasks and investigations\u003C/li\u003E        \u003Cli\u003ESpecific instructions for patient monitoring\u003C/li\u003E        \u003Cli\u003EClear escalation parameters\u003C/li\u003E    \u003C/ul\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Effective clinical handovers must include patient identification, clinical status, outstanding tasks, and early warning signs.","Omitting critical information during handover can lead to adverse patient outcomes and care discontinuity.","Structured handover frameworks help ensure comprehensive information transfer between healthcare teams."],"references":["Desmedt M, Ulenaers D, Grosemans J, Hellings J, Bergs J. Clinical handover and handoff in healthcare: a systematic review of systematic reviews. Int J Qual Health Care. 2021 Feb 20;33(1):mzaa170. doi: 10.1093/intqhc/mzaa170. PMID: 33325520. Available at: https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/33325520/","Australian Commission on Safety and Quality in Health Care. Communication at clinical handover [online]. Accessed 15 Jan 2025. Available at: https://www.safetyandquality.gov.au/standards/nsqhs-standards/communicating-safety-standard/communication-clinical-handover","Medical Board of Australia. Good medical practice: a code of conduct for doctors in Australia [online]. 2020 [Cited 2025 Jan 15]. Available at: https://www.medicalboard.gov.au/codes-guidelines-policies/code-of-conduct.aspx"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"70360"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18858"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"70360","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/70360"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-02-19T10:27:05+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-02-19T10:28:13+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11591"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"86095"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"ty